This paper focuses on improving the quality of bug reports, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE). The approach proposed, Euler, involves automatically identifying and assessing the quality of the steps to reproduce in bug reports, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques (cs.PL, cs.AI). The goal of Euler is to provide feedback to the reporters, which can improve the quality of the bug report, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper also discusses related work on bug report quality assessment, which involves information retrieval techniques (cs.IR).
